Sentencas: In the sealing system of Ni-YSZ anode/SrO-MgO-SiO2 glass-ceramic sealant/430 s s. interconnect, the phase transformation and mechanical properties of interfaces are studied after operating 0 h, 100 h, and 1800 h at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Study of high temperature mechanical properties and damage behavior of Ni-YSZ anode/SrO -MgO -SiO 2 glass-ceramic sealant/430 s.s. interconnect system in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC)

Sentencas: The results show that the interface fracture appears in the glass/anode and glass/interconnect interfaces after operating at 1800 h.
Titulo: Study of high temperature mechanical properties and damage behavior of Ni-YSZ anode/SrO -MgO -SiO 2 glass-ceramic sealant/430 s.s. interconnect system in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC)

Sentencas: The interface mechanical parameters within different operation times are collected to investigate the effects of crystallization, penetration, and high temperature mechanical properties on the interlayer stress and structure damage.
Titulo: Study of high temperature mechanical properties and damage behavior of Ni-YSZ anode/SrO -MgO -SiO 2 glass-ceramic sealant/430 s.s. interconnect system in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC)

Sentencas: The Sr2MgSi2O7 crystal phase increases the glass modulus from 104.5 GPa to 129.8 GPa with a runtime from 0 h to 1800 h. The modulus of the Ni-YSZ interface also increases from 82.4 GPa to 128.3 GPa with the glass penetration process.
Titulo: Study of high temperature mechanical properties and damage behavior of Ni-YSZ anode/SrO -MgO -SiO 2 glass-ceramic sealant/430 s.s. interconnect system in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC)

Sentencas: The 430 s s. modulus is reduced by 13 % at 750 degrees C after 1800 h to reach 191.1 GPa.
Titulo: Study of high temperature mechanical properties and damage behavior of Ni-YSZ anode/SrO -MgO -SiO 2 glass-ceramic sealant/430 s.s. interconnect system in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC)
